
MSNBC-TV's Monica Novotny blogs: "Money goes a long way in making your life easier in this city. But it is also the capital of "the things money can't buy.? According to a Daily News report one of the "terror tip" emails was dated October 3, 6:05 pm ... "about ninety minutes before the Mayor was fully briefed on the threat." It appears our very own mayor, worth billions, didn't get the email. This one's not about money. It's about access."

